			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Polyvinyl chloride (PVC) is a versatile and economical material used in various sectors, such as building and construction, packaging, healthcare and household products. It is the third most manufactured plastic in use today. PVC is a thermoplastic that is a polymer of vinyl chloride. Resins of PVC are hard, but with the addition of plasticizers a flexible, elastic plastic can be made. This plastic has found extensive use as an electrical insulator for wires and cables.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">聚氯乙烯（PVC）是一种用途广泛、经济实惠的材料，广泛应用于建筑、包装、医疗保健和家用产品等各个领域。聚氯乙烯是一种热塑性塑料，是氯乙烯的聚合物。PVC 是一种热塑性塑料，是氯乙烯的聚合物。聚氯乙烯的树脂很硬，但加入增塑剂后可以制成柔韧而有弹性的塑料。这种塑料被广泛用作电线电缆的绝缘体。</common:generalComment>
